label.value: acute disease course

definition.value: a disease course with a rapid onset but typical unfolding of signs and symptoms after this rapid onset.

label.value: vegetative amoebae

value.value: Unicellular haploid myxamoebae that feeds on bacteria by phagocytosis and divides by binary fission. The size of vegetative cells range from 12-20 microns by 8-12 microns. The cells exhibit a roughly rounded but rather irregular shape.

label.value: aggregation territory

value.value: Area covered by a group of chemotactic cells converging toward the same aggregation center. Can reach a diameter of up to 1 cm.

label.value: loose aggregate

value.value: First adherent mass of cells observed during development, relatively flat with indistinct borders.

label.value: mound

value.value: Hemispherical structure composed of post-aggregative cells that are undergoing differentiation.

label.value: tipped mound

value.value: Hemispherical structure composed of post-aggregative cells that are undergoing differentiation and that have formed a tip.

label.value: standing slug

value.value: Cylindrical structure that is formed by elongation of the mound under the control of the tip. The elongating tip is called the first finger.

label.value: migratory slug

value.value: When the conditions are not optimal for the completion of development, the standing slug bends from a vertical position to a horizontal position, producing a migratory that slug has the ability to migrate towards more favorable environmental conditions. The slug is cylindrical in shape with a rounded, tapering region at its anterior end that is raised with respect to the substratum. It usually measures between 0.8 to 1.2 mm in length with a diameter of 0.15 to 0.25 mm. Slugs sense and respond to light, temperature and acidity, and do not enter culmination until the conditions are optimal. The slug can move at a speed of 0.5 to 2 mm per hour. A trail of slime is deposited on the surface during migration.

label.value: early culminant

value.value: Structure formed after the arrest of slug migration formed when cells of the posterior region of the slug move under the tip. Stalk tube formation is initiated at this stage.

label.value: mid culminant

value.value: Structure in which stalk tube formation has progressed down the prespore zone. Basal disc formation begins at this stage, with the migration of pstA and pstB cells to the lower part of the culminant to form the basal disc.

label.value: late culminant

value.value: Structure in which stalk tube formation has progressed down to the basal disc. The sorogen ascents up the stalk to it apical position during this stage. Terminal differentiation occurs at this stage: death of the stalk cells and encapsulation of the spores.

label.value: fruiting body

value.value: Dicty asexual organism which is terminally differentiated and consists of a long stalk on top of which sits the sorus that contains spores. The mature fruiting body measures between 1.5 to 3 mm in height.

label.value: stream

value.value: Macroscopic appearance of groups of chemotactic cells orienting themselves in a head to tail fashion as they are migrating in the direction of the chemotactic stimulus to form aggregates.

label.value: surface sheath of the loose aggregate

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins, formed during late aggregation and that holds the cell mass together in the aggregate.

label.value: surface sheath of the mound

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins that holds the cell mass together in the mound.

label.value: prestalk region of the tipped mound

value.value: Elongated protusion of the tipped mound located on top of the cell mass that contains pstA cells flanked by pstO cells (expressing ecmA from the proximal and the distal part of its promoter, respectively).

label.value: prespore region of the tipped mound

value.value: Region of the tipped mound mostly composed of prespore cells. In addition to prespore cells, the prespore region contains anterior-like cells (ALC) that express ecmA and/or ecmB.

label.value: surface sheath of the tipped mound

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins that holds the cell mass together in the tipped mound.

label.value: prestalk region of the standing slug

value.value: Elongated protrusion of the standing slug located on top of the cell mass that contains pstA cells flanked by pstO cells (expressing ecmA from the proximal and the distal part of its promoter, respectively).

label.value: tip-organizer of the standing slug

value.value: Part of the prestalk region of the standing slug that acts as an organizer, that is, a signalling center that directs the morphological characteristics of the entire organism.

label.value: prestalk A region of the standing slug

value.value: Most apical region of the prestalk zone of the standing slug characterized by high expression of the ecmA gene directed by the proximal part of its promoter (ecmA promoter).

label.value: prestalk O region of the standing slug

value.value: Area of the prestalk zone of the standing slug located posterior to the prestalk A region and characterized by low expression of the ecmA gene directed by the distal part of its promoter (ecmO promoter).

label.value: prestalk AB core region of the standing slug

value.value: Cone-shaped area of the prestalk zone of the standing slug that occupies a core among the pstA region. Cells of the pstAB region express both the ecmA and ecmB genes.

label.value: prespore region of the standing slug

value.value: Region of the standing slug mostly composed of prespore cells. In addition to prespore cells, the prespore region contains anterior-like cells (ALC) that express ecmA and/or ecmB. The prespore region occupies about three quarters of the organism.

label.value: basal region of the standing slug

value.value: Region of the standing slug in contact with the substratum and composed of prestalk B cells.

label.value: peripheral layer of the standing slug

value.value: Outer-most cell layer surrounding the standing slug. The peripheral layer is composed of electron-dense cells that are connected to each other, forming a coherent tissue.

label.value: surface sheath of the standing slug

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins that holds the cell mass together in the standing slug.

label.value: prestalk region of the migratory slug

value.value: The prestalk region of the migratory slug is located at the anterior of the organism. It consists of about one quarter of the cells.

label.value: tip-organizer of the migratory slug

value.value: Part of the prestalk region of the migratory slug that acts as an organizer, that is, a signalling center that directs the morphological characteristics of the entire organism. The tip guides the movement of the organism during migration.

label.value: prestalk A region of the migratory slug

value.value: Anterior-most region of the prestalk zone of the migratory slug and characterized by high expression of the ecmA gene directed by the proximal part of its promoter (ecmA promoter).

label.value: prestalk O region of the migratory slug

value.value: Area of the prestalk zone of the migratory slug located posterior to the prestalk A region and characterized by low expression of the ecmA gene directed by the distal part of its promoter (ecmO promoter).

label.value: prestalk AB core region of the migratory slug

value.value: Cone-shaped area of the prestalk zone of the migratory slug that occupies a core among the pstA region. Cells of the pstAB region express both the ecmA and ecmB genes.

label.value: prespore region of the migratory slug

value.value: Region of the migratory slug composed mostly of prespore cells. In addition to prespore cells, the prespore region contains anterior-like cells (ALC) that express ecmA and/or ecmB. The prespore region occupies about three quarters of the organism.

label.value: posterior region of the migratory slug

value.value: Region located at the very posterior of the migratory slug that contains pstB cells (rearguard cells). These cells form the basal disc in the mature fruiting body.

label.value: peripheral layer of the migratory slug

value.value: Outer-most cell layer surrounding the migratory slug. The peripheral layer is composed of electron-dense cells that are connected to each other, forming a coherent tissue.

label.value: surface sheath of the migratory slug

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins that holds the cell mass together in the migratory slug.

label.value: prestalk region of the early culminant

value.value: The prestalk region of the early culminant is located at the most apical part of the organism. It consists of about one quarter of the cells.

label.value: prestalk A region of the early culminant

value.value: Anterior-most region of the prestalk zone of the early culminant characterized by high expression of the ecmA gene directed by the proximal part of its promoter (ecmA promoter).

label.value: prestalk O region of the early culminant

value.value: Area of the prestalk zone of the early culminant located posterior to the pstA region and characterized by low expression of the ecmA gene directed by the distal part of its promoter (ecmO promoter).

label.value: prestalk AB core region of the early culminant

value.value: Cone-shaped area of the prestalk zone of the early culminant that occupies a core among the pstA region. Cells of the pstAB region express both the ecmA and ecmB genes.

label.value: prespore region of the early culminant

value.value: Region of the early culminant mostly composed of prespore cells. In addition to prespore cells, the prespore region contains anterior-like cells (ALC) that express ecmA and/or ecmB. The prespore region occupies about three quarters of the organism.

label.value: upper cup region of the early culminant

value.value: Region of the prespore zone of the early culminant that borders the prestalk region. This region gives rise to the upper cup of the fruiting body.

label.value: stalk tube of the early culminant

value.value: Open, cylindrical tube of the early culminant composed of cellulose and glycoprotein and surrounded by a ring of actin in which stalk cells accumulate.

label.value: prespore/base region of the early culminant

value.value: Region of the prespore zone of the early culminant that borders the base. This region gives rise to the lower cup of the fruiting body.

label.value: basal region of the early culminant

value.value: Region of the early culminant located at the closest to the substratum composed of pstB cells that originated from rearguard cells.

label.value: peripheral layer of the early culminant

value.value: Layer surrounding the mexican hat and composed of an electron-dense cell type.

label.value: surface sheath of the early culminant

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins that holds the cell mass together in the early culminant.

label.value: prestalk region of the mid culminant

value.value: The prestalk region of the mid culminant is located at the most apical part of the organism. It consists of about one quarter of the cells.

label.value: prestalk A region of the mid culminant

value.value: Anterior-most region of the prestalk zone of the mid culminant characterized by high expression of the ecmA gene directed by the proximal part of its promoter (ecmA promoter).

label.value: prestalk O region of the mid culminant

value.value: Area of the prestalk zone of the mid culminant located posterior to the prestalk A region and characterized by low expression of the ecmA gene directed by the distal part of its promoter (ecmO promoter).
